--> Key Insights

1. Gender has almost no effect on spending — average spend is nearly identical between Male and Female customers (~$455–457).
2. Age is not a strong predictor of spend (correlation ≈ -0.06) — customers of all ages spend similarly.
3. Product Category is fairly balanced: Electronics leads in total revenue, Clothing has the most transactions, Beauty has the highest average order value.
4. Monthly revenue fluctuates rather than following one seasonal peak — May and October are the strongest months, September the weakest.
5. What actually drives spend: Price per Unit (r ≈ 0.85) and Quantity (r ≈ 0.37) — far more than any demographic factor.
6. Price spread varies by category — Electronics shows the widest price range, Beauty is more tightly clustered.


